The Kuwaiti papers said they hoped the Jiddah meeting was the start of a final just settlement of the differences between Iraq and Kuwait, in a manner ensuring the legitimate rights of each.  for Kuwait . Kuwait and the UAE agreed to stick to their oil quotas at an OPEC meeting last week. Saddam also demanded compensation for the $2. The Iraq-Kuwait crisis broke out on July 17 when Iraqi President Saddam Hussein accused Kuwait and the United Arab Emirates of driving down oil prices by exceeding quotas set for them by the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries. 